56.6929133858267775 586.7718897637794271 Td
(1. Library Installation: I used the Node Package Manager \(npm\) to download and install both) Tj
T* (   'jspdf' and 'jspdf-autotable' into the project.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (2. PDF Document Setup: I created a utility function that initializes a new PDF document.) Tj
T* (   Because there are 28 fields, I configured the PDF to be in landscape orientation and) Tj
T* (   used an A3 page size to ensure all the columns would fit without overlapping.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (3. Data Structuring: I mapped over the employee data to extract the 28 required fields.) Tj
T* (   For fields that can have multiple items \(like RAM sticks, Storage drives, and GPUs\),) Tj
T* (   I programmed it to combine all the items using line breaks so they display neatly) Tj
T* (   inside a single cell for that specific employee.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (4. Table Generation: I fed the structured headers and the mapped employee data into) Tj
T* (   the 'autotable' plugin. I customized the table theme by coloring the headers dark) Tj
T* (   blue \(to match the web app's theme\), reducing the font size, and enabling automatic) Tj
T* (   line breaking for long text.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (5. Interface Integration: Finally, I updated the main application interface by adding) Tj
T* (   an 'Export PDF' button to the toolbar. This button takes whatever list of devices) Tj
T* (   is currently filtered on your screen and triggers the utility function to download) Tj
T* (   the customized PDF file to your computer.) Tj
ET
